      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A sharp, intermittent squeal is often more indicative of a specific issue than a constant grind. It could certainly be a sensor, like a wear indicator, that is just starting to engage, or perhaps a piece of metal rubbing against the rotor. If you've checked the caliper and it seems fine, you might want to take a closer look at the brake pad material itself. Sometimes, the pads need a little \"break-in\" time to seat properly against the rotor, which can cause a high-pitched squeak initially.",
